                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1151</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-27T23:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1917—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Wireless reports from number of naval vessels indicate most unsatisfactory
                    conditions in Cuba yesterday existed in immediate vicinity Guantanamo where 220
                    marines landed. Landing of two companies marines from U. S. S. <hi rend="italic"
                        >Connecticut</hi> also reported but place not stated. May be at San
                    Francisco about thirty miles west of Manzanillo.</p>
                <p>No late military developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
